779. Argis: Argos (in Latin more frequently Argi, nom. pl), the capital of Argolis in the Peloponnese. It was but a few miles south- ward from Mycenae, the capital of Agamemnon, with which it is often confused in the legends. though in origin a later town whose Subsequent importance quite ruined Mycenae.
